caption.text:
Even clones deserve coffee break. .
.

Happy international coffee day! Coffee is very easily my drug of choice- if I had to choose between coffee, and all the various types of alcoholic beverages and herbal buds in the world- coffee would win out every time. I wanted to do a super quick shot to celebrate the day and having Scarlet Spider show up this week complete with  coffee and a cell phone (two things that were truly meant for one another 😂), the shot couldn’t have made itself more clear. Perhaps at first glance this looks like a digirama or something similar, but it’s not- Ben here is chilling on the ledge of the top floor of my parking garage and I’m just using actual downtown San Diego as my backdrop. I had other shots that I took that showed off the city skyline a little better, but something about this one just screamed out to me saying ‘pick me! I’m the one!’ And who am I to not listen to my own coffee fueled hallucinations?? .
.

Scarlet Spider 1/6 scale figure, meticulously created and crafted by the masters that are @hottoyscollectibles (thank you for making my dream figure a reality!) .
.

caption.text:
Lets talk nostalgia here for a sec! 
Today I went to a flea market and found this gem for 50 cents! A 1998 Pokémon action set book! It’s basically a book filled with mini cardboard cutouts to take pictures of. This was basically The 1998 version of go snapshot, place your figures on one of the backgrounds and take a pic! 
It is super fun to look at the 90s style and relive my chlildhood with this book but I don’t know what they were thinking about when scaling some of the Pokémon... Look at the size of that meowth! #babey
_

_

It was raining as Dream and I lined up at the starting line at Valedale Lake. As soon as the buzzer rang, I squeezed Dream and he immediately started into a gallop, ears forward and at attention. I directed him to the first jump: a simple log. He practically soared over it. Next up was a series of steps we had to jump down. Perfect. As we got to the bottom of the steps, it began to rain harder and it became hard to see where I was going. Next was a water combination. Half way through the combination, there was a loud clap of thunder. I thought that as usual, my silver boy would just ignore it and do his job. Completely forgetting about the accident, I nudged Dream forward and asked for a bigger canter. He stuck his ears back and reared up, causing me to slide off his back into the water. Great. Just great.

Today was the day where I said to myself "this is a relax day. Dont go wild about doing ANYTHING today." And I didn't. I got up later than usual, ate breakfast (I dont know what that is anymore so imagine me looking at a cereal bowl whispering questioningly "what is... breakfast.") Barely did makeup, just mascara and lipstick, played ACNL and ANPC, went for a smol stroll and laid back in bed again. I constantly want to do something fun, but at the same time its draining me. Its making my head hurt, making myself tired on purpose and freaking out over everything. When all I need to do sometimes.. is SIT MY ASS DOWN AND GIVE MYSELF A DAY FOR ME. And it felt good. .
.
.

caption.text:
Happy 23rd anniversary to the N64 and Super Mario 64. Released, on September 29, 1996 in North America, the N64 was so memorable to our household. I remember my brother washing so many cars in order to save as much as could towards the purchase of this system. He got to unwrap it for Christmas that year. Super Mario 64 was such a departure from of the previous Mario games we had played before, but it just translated so perfectly. The game took longer to finish than it should of because I was determined to get all 120 stars.  I've recently been thinking hard about firing the system back up, and playing some of our favorites. If I do, it'll be tough to choose what to play first. .

Fabian Malabello - The Otherworld Agency / Boss Battle Records
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
@fabian_otherworld is an agent, a BAFTA-winning music supervisor, and the director of The Otherworld Agency, and @bossbattlerecords.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Fabian, via The Otherworld Agency (founded in 2015), represents over 40 composers and sound designers across the globe, and has provided audio services to companies such as Konami, Bandai-Namco, Honda, Acura, Chucklefish, and THQ Nordic, among dozens more. In 2018, MCV Pacific named Fabian as one of the 2017 MCV Pacific 30 Under Thirty class, an initiative to recognise the brightest young talent across the Australian and New Zealand video game industries.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
After founding Boss Battle Records in 2017, Fabian inked a label partnership deal with @remotecontrolrecords, one of Australia’s premier indie record labels. Boss Battle Records is a video game music record label, which is working with major and indie game publishers from around the world.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Fabian additionally coordinates and curates game audio conferences, symphonic concerts, and guest lectures at colleges such as Berklee College of Music. 
Twitter: @FMalabello

This movie is gonna be a masterpiece

The Legend of Zelda. Would it surprise you to find out that I haven't actually played this game much at all? I was just too young at the time to get it. The adventure begins, you go into a cave and get a sword, then...? The few times I played it as a kid, I was just completely lost from the start and just had no idea what I was supposed to do or where I was supposed to go. Now that I'm older I realize that's actually part of the appeal - that sense of exploration and discovery. But that was a little beyond 4 year old me at the time. It also didn't help that this is a game I only had a chance to play for only like 15 minutes at a time at either a friend's place or a family get together. This is more of a game that you need some time to get absorbed into. 
Since I just didn't understand it when I was young, this is a game that I just never requested for any birthday or Christmas. Due to that, it's a classic that eluded my collection throughout my childhood. I didn't actually get into the Zelda series until the Gameboy with Link's Awakening. Later on there was a promotional disc for the GameCube that included both NES games in it. I didn't have that one, but my friend Mike did, so I sat in his dorm and watched him play for several hours. Later on my other friend Steve emulated the game on his computer and I watched him play it as well.

This copy was actually a recent acquisition from a friend from work, Andi. He's kind of become my video game dealer. He keeps giving me really good deals on old games that I just can't pass up on. This is one of those great deals. The box and contents are in awesome condition. It'll finally allow me to right the wrong of not playing it in my youth!
